title: How to Make a Chocolate Cherry Snack Cake

steps.headline: Spray an 8 to 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

Snip the maraschino cherries with a pair of kitchen scissors or use a sharp knife to cut them up.

steps.description: Fill the cup to make 1 cup of liquid total.

steps.headline: Add the syrup-water mixture to the pan.

steps.headline: Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

text: Spray an 8 to 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.  Preheat oven to 350ºF or 180ºC.  Add dry ingredients to prepared baking pan.  Combine dry ingredients with a fork.  Snip the maraschino cherries with a pair of kitchen scissors or use a sharp knife to cut them up.  Add the cherries to the pan.  Add reserved maraschino cherry syrup to a glass measuring cup. Fill the cup to make 1 cup of liquid total. Add the syrup-water mixture to the pan. Mix with a fork until a batter forms. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.  Serves 9.
